rows.title: KRAKAKAKOOM!!!
rows.titleText:
On a bright afternoon, the sky splits open as the earth is struck seven times. 
Heralding the birth of a child of crimson! Each strike will be a trial, a labour. 
Either you stand and be worthy of your blood or fail like the many before you. 
You are of the crimson, the crimson is of you. 
It burns through your body igniting your blood, demanding glory and sin. You feel within you the power to grasp and do the impossible, to break the unbreakable.
Let your legend burn brighter than the two suns that grace Ascarnia. 
Your saga’s will be written in crimson. 

Now come child, before all that tell me of your origins.

rows.title: Origin
rows.titleText: Now, child of crimson...What ilk sired you?

objects.title: Human
objects.text:
Of those who came before, of those who built and were broken in return. Humanity though not a majority have spread far across the land of Atresus. Humans come in many shapes and sizes, with skin tones ranging from pale as sunlight to dark as wood.

Gain free will.

objects.title: Ork
objects.text:
A race whose blood is steeped in war, who’s ears know the siren song of battle. The orcs are the horde the horde are the orcs. No other race throughout Atresus knows battle like that of the orcs. They fight all that can be fought, they kill all that can be killed and even sometimes those that cannot. Seen as both noble and babaric. 
Their people are the only thing that stands between the greater world and the deadlands.

objects.title: minotaur
objects.text: The emerald fields are your home, the peaceful lands of the north. Where the lands give in abundance. Where food is not scarce, and neighbour does not kill neighbour. The land provides and in return you care for it. Harmony with nature is found here.

objects.title: Elfen
objects.text: The of the dread forest. Where dire beasts and horrors walk through the canopy of leaves, where trees that seem to touch the sky reach out, their branches like roads. None know the horrors of nature like elfen do. Who maintain their cultures and societies through large communes, where each plays are role in the cycle of things. If you fail to do your part then you are given to the wilds, let them decide your fate. Magik is unknown to you and will never be known to you. And you care little for it. All you really and need is the green. The rest is just noise.

objects.title: Goblin
objects.text: Some call these a lesser race for their small stature and weak body. Let not the words of fools poison thine mind. For what they lack in size, they make up for in malicious cunning. None can compete with the Goblen when it comes to alchemy for the deadliest of poisons and philtres come from the dark tribes. For these vicious creatures have prayed to the Crimson their whole lives, giving blood and sweat and sin. None are so favoured as the Goblen when it comes to the crimson, gifting them keen intellect for the wicked. Your time may be few on this world, but you are one of the few who know how to make the most of it.

rows.title: Lesser Abilities
rows.titleText: Take as many as the fruits of your labour can afford you.

objects.title: Strength
objects.text: There are those born with strength and then there are those born with something beyond strength. To split boulders with a swing of your fist, to wrestle beasts with you’re bare hands, two mould iron as though it were clay. Yours isn’t just strength but durability as well. No hammer can be stronger nor weaker than the metal it was forged with. Still there are things out there that can break a hammer.

objects.title: Celerity
objects.text: You have seen the drakes and found envy of their freedom. You want for their speed, able to cross what would take a man days in mere hours. Your lust had driven you to attain such. Though they be faster you have come close enough. In battle your movements are a blur to the untrained eyes. Though there are those both beast and man who’s speed can rival your own.

objects.title: Magiks
objects.text: The raw sorcerers that bend the world and reality around them. Imposing what you believe to be true. Harness the stellar waves, call to the cosmic squids that spread through the stars. Commune with the astral phoenixes learn of the world between. However, there is risk with what you work with. For Magiks can be unforgiving. Any small mistake can lead to your slow and painful demise. Causing an eternity of pain and torment to be experienced within a fraction of a second. The crimson will not care, the crimson will not pity.

objects.title: Alchemy
objects.text: The alchemy to take the marvellous, the mundane and make improbable possible. To capture a cats footsteps and a mountain's roots and to create philtres and potions. Create fiends flame mixes and Astral gales. Even mundane materials such as gunpowder can be made. Though alchemy can be unpredictable. Many are those who have died before mastering their crafts.

objects.title: Smithery
objects.text: The metal whispers to you asking. Asking for you hands to give them form. You have learnt to build all manner of things made metal. From swords, to shields to armour and even the mundane nails, hinges and pots. You have learnt to shape metal in all manner of things. In time and with training and practice what you make will may considered masterworks. Each taking less time and being of a higher quality than the last. Though the works of old are beyond even your gift.

objects.title: Runemaster
objects.text: You bend the world in your own way imposing your will through mark and carving. You understand the language of the universe. The dragons had mastered this, before moving to greater works. Though in that time they created wonders and horrors alike with the use of one single rune. You will only understand a sliver of this, but a sliver is more than enough.

objects.title: Regeneration
objects.text: You heal faster than you should. Wounds mending in the heat of battle, bones snapping back in place, cuts sealing in moments. You have never known sickness and poisons are only 10% effective on you. However, there is a limit to how effective this is. The more wounds and poisons you take at once the less effective it becomes. You’ll heal slower. You are not invincible, the crimson does not tolerate fools. Remember that. Use what you have to your advantage but do not come to rely on it. NOTHING IS INFALLIBLE.

objects.title: Adaptability
objects.text:
Humanity is known for its adaptability. Though this trait has shown itself to spring up with halfbloods. Always when you find yourself at the brink of death, your body does not answer the call of Dovka. Instead it fights on.
 What hurt you yesterday has less of an effect than it did on you today. 
Though the growth will always be marginal. You will not see the fruits of your labour till you reach old age. Till your hairs turn grey and yours eyes clouded. 
Compounds well with berserker.

objects.title: Forked tongue
objects.text: Yours is the way of word. To charm and lie, to cheat and seduce. You have a way with words others do no. You know how to get the right discounts. You know the right people and so on.

objects.title: Will
objects.text: To do what must be done. To go passed pain and misery, passed hell and even heaven. Once you have made a choice you will see it done.  Your will is great, greater than any mind control. You do exactly as you say. What the spirit wants, the mind will understand, and the body will achieve. This doesn’t mean your are capable of doing anything. It means as long as you have the knowledge, the resources, the skills and time. There is nothing mundane you cannot learn. This skill greatly compound others.

objects.title: Mute
objects.text: Sorceries roll of you like summer rain, runes frizzle and pop before reaching you. Curses and hexes are nothing but hot air from the mouth of fools. Direct attacks through these methods are pointless they do nothing to you. Mind you that doesn’t stop someone from hurling rocks or trees on you. You are a mute. Magiks and their effects are lost to you. You cannot call for aid from flame, and magical beings avoid you like the plague. Expect magically inclined allies and companions to find your very presence disturbing. Even alchemies cannot aid you their healing properties ravaged by your soul. Magikal blades and armour will be useless, just steel and iron. You cannot control mutes effects.

objects.title: Berserker
objects.text: Shield biter, berserker syndrome, mad wolf blooded, the black rage these are some of the names used to refer to your affliction. Something simmers within you hot and foul. Wanting nothing but destruction, to spill the blood of both friend and foe of sinner and innocent. To the bleed and rend. Many berserks die young. Either loosing a battle or put down by the very people you’ve called ally. You can count the number of berserks of reached old age on but one hand. You have lived longer than most.

objects.title: Survival
objects.text: You know nature you know survival. You have been tempered. The cold does not rob your body of its warmth, nor does the heat rob you of your water. Be it at the tallest mountain or in the thickest jungle. You can make a home for yourself and thrive. Your body is efficient claiming almost every piece of nutrients and fat ingested. You can last months and weeks without water. You require only 4 hours of sleep a month.

objects.title: WeaponsMaster
objects.text:
In your hands blades hum and arrows sing. No dagger nor spear will ever be sharper than the one in your hands. Be it a club or shield there is no weapon unknown to you. You learn in weeks what masters take years to learn. 
The more exotic the longer it will take to master a weapon.

objects.title: To cut
objects.text: You walk a path of enlightnment few have dared to set foot upon. With spear, dagger or sword you have learnt to split. Distance matters little to you, only the sharpness of your tool and the harmony that you have cultivated after a lifetime of spilling objects. Be it an enemy who stands before you or one a few blocks over. You will cut them down, the only thing that would give you pause are the people and object between you and them. Unless that too doesnt matter to you.

objects.title: Tatakae
objects.text:
Be it through fear, bribery, inspiration or a mix of all of the above. You are able to turn a coward into a fearless soldier who will walk with you through hell and back. With time you can take the most spineless, lilylivered yellow bellied mob into a capable fighting force. As long as you can teach them to fight that is. 
This can be used to inspire armies or encourage allies. If you fight side by side with them the effect is doubled.

rows.title: Greater Abilities
rows.titleText: Through every battle and every challenge, your abilities have grown. Through trials and tribulation, the crimson had dubbed you worthy. Some of your abilities have grown, becoming more than their sum of parts.

objects.title: Denial
objects.text: To deny is to believe your will greater than what is taking place, a sorceress hurls lighting at you, you deny it ever striking. If your will is greater there is almost nothing that can affect you. Now after mastering the abilities of mute through sheer will you can control its effects. You can deny what you please and accept what you desire. Healing works slightly better as though the magiks accept your supremacy over them. Can now deny direct effects of magik as long as your will is greater than the caster. With time and practice and suffering you can learn to turn the mightiest blows that can sheer through mountains. You start at the bottom with the bare bone’s abilities. Nothing will be handed to you crimson. You will earn it or fail.

objects.title: True rage
objects.text: Yours is no longer the mindless destruction of hot rage, nor is it tame. You have come upon a lesser truth of being. Your rage is that of a cool burning, scorching away the fog of your emotions. Yours is the calm rage, the rage that brings clarity, the rage that when guided will bring unparallel destruction. A cool and directed force, I pity the fool in its way. You are no longer the shield biter but the rage guider.

objects.title: Outer sorcery
objects.text: Failure is not an option, with your will guiding your works. The dangers of the unforeseen world are only secondary. Nothing sorcerous is beyond your grasp. Learn of the dreadful arts from Deadking Ottar the foul. Unleash the unholy mistress that made the celestials turn from Atreseus. All you need is time. Create spells and effects that can span a whole continent. Within your mind is the power to split the sky with but a word

objects.title: Artifact creator
objects.text: To create is to believe that what you make will be better than that which already exists. The metal answers you, the metal yields to you.  The stone sings to you telling tales of old, the flames of the forge will never burn you, nothing you forge will ever hurt you. With this you can create wonders, blades that carry the kiss an infernal, shields that believe themselves to be as sturdy as mountains, staffs that harness the ethereal, boots that carry the footfalls of cat.

objects.title: Pankration
objects.text:
You need no greater sorcery, you need no mind trick, you need no denial, no hiding behind berserkings and emotions. For what is it to deny what is true. No, yours is something purer something truer. Yours is the road of attrition, the path of endurance the path that goes beyond strength. To swing of your fists with enough strength to hurl gusts of wind, to look up at the skies and lunge with enough strength to rip wyverns from the sky. To split mountains with a single strike. The winds have kissed your feet and dubbed the worthy of their gift. Leagues mean nothing to you now. With your blessings and endurance, no distance is too far. No place as long as there is a path, is unreachable. You accept all attacks as what they are taking both sorcery and blade without flinching. Waiting and ready to strike. Sorcery and armour is wasted on you for what weapon is greater than your fist, what shield stronger than your body. Only abilities from the great ability’s sections will wound your flesh, only they will turn your fist. The only question is for how long. The lesser abilities are nothing to you only bring pain, but what is pain to the enduring mountain? What is agony to the crimson?
Nothing but the words of those beneath you.

objects.title: Philosopher’s stone
objects.text: Your alchemis have reached the pinnacle, you have gained an understanding many have devoted whole bloodline to finding and still have failed. You have managed to create Materia prima, the next element or better known as the philosopher’s stone. The perfect element imbeds itself within you. And with its merging comes the wonders of eternal youth, you are brought back to your prime, your body has gains abilities rival regeneration, strength and survival in its potency. Though not nearly enough if you had been born with these traits. Still this puts you leagues above others in the world.

objects.title: The darwin
objects.text: Your alchemis have reached the pinnacle, you have gained an understanding many have devoted whole bloodline to finding and still have failed. You have managed to create Materia prima, the next element or better known as the philosopher’s stone. The perfect element imbeds itself within you. And with its merging comes the wonders of eternal youth, you are brought back to your prime, your body has gains abilities rival regeneration, strength and survival in its potency. Though not nearly enough if you had been born with these traits. Still this puts you leagues above others in the world.

objects.title: To sever
objects.text: To cut, to sever, to seperate. You have reached the pinacle of this ability. There is no need for a blade, spear or dagger. The mere act of waving your hand is enough. Be it flesh, stone or spell. Yours is the divine act of parting. Though those with a greater abilitywill require more effort to part than those without.

objects.title: Warmaster
objects.text:
You need no soft words, no harsh whip nor any goldne coins. Men and weapon see you and feel the need to do better with themselves. To strive with all your might, to achieve even a sliver of what you carry within you. 
Weapons masters whove dedicated themselves to a single weapon will weep with joy as they watch your techniques. 
Soldiers will rally and hold the line at the mear mention of your name.
The moment you set foot within a battlefield half the fight is won.

rows.title: Drawbacks
rows.titleText:
Let us hear of your difficulties young crimson. Remember the crimson coddles no one, it is advisable to take at least one drawback. Though be warned any more than that and you will face injury and even grave death long before your sagas can be written. Who’s death? that all depends. Remember this crimson, for through great adversary do the worthy ride. So tell me yee of crimson are you worthy to rise? 
Be careful in what you pick once you pick them there's no going back.(It will be buggy if you select and deselect.)
For each extra drawback you take you can take another greater ability you qualify for.

objects.title: Chronic pains
objects.text: Every so often, a pain in either your back, neck or shoulders will flare up becoming deliberating. Philtres and potions will ease this somewhat, but it will always be there gnawing at the back of your mind every time it flares up. The philtres are expensive and hard to find. Unless you are an alchemist then you can make them. But they will take up time. Up to two weeks to finish a batch. It can flare up after battle, or after sitting or laying in a position for too long. The pain is deep like red hot nails being driven into the affected areas. Your body will become stiff, and any movement you make will send waves of pain through your body. Sleep will be impossible leaving you exhausted and sluggish. The pain can last for a few moments to a few weeks to even two months. The longer periods will be rare, whilst the shorter ones will be more frequent.  Sometimes it can flare up at inopportune time i.e in the middle of a battle. With the WILL perk, you can power through this though it will take considerable effort on your side.

objects.title: Rival
objects.text:
You have slighted someone within the companion list. They hold a deep grudge against you. Either it is due to something you did or they believe you undeserving of your place in the world. They will stop at nothing to show they are better than you. They aren’t necessarily evil, but they are petty. And will always strive to be better than you. Pick one ability you have, they have more skill in this than you. If it is strength they are slightly stronger than you, if its celerity they are only marginally faster than you. In a battle of life and death sometimes that is all they need to make a difference. With time and every defeat or failure, they will grow bitter. Their pettiness twisting into pure malice. It is not impossible to turn them to your side or to make peace with them. It will cost you though and will take great effort, patience and wit to do so. And by the end of it, it might not be worth it anymore. If you fail to turn them to your side they will gain a GREATER ABILITY more potent than yours. 
If you defeat them, pick two more lesser abilities.

objects.title: Nemesis
objects.text:
This personal is the opposite of your beliefs. If you believe all men should be free, then they believe anyone without a collar should be brutally and publicly executed. If you believe your will matters above all else they believe that the will of the people matters more than that of some despot. They will do everything in their power to ensure everything you hope to achieve is made impossible. They are vicious and relentless, expect to meet opposition on every plan you make. You will have three chances and only three to defeat them. If you fail to do so, it will lead to an altercation at one of your saga. This will double the difficulty, you will not leave that saga unscathed and may actually meet defeat. 
Encounters will take place at each quest adding to the difficulty. 
Roll a 3d20
1-10= failure
11-16=draw
17-20=Pass
If you fail twice take the chronic pain drawback with no perk. If you fail thrice they will kill one of your companions and gain a greater ability twice as potent as your. The fourth time you meet will be the end of you. DO NOT FAIL. Or fail…the crimson cares not. 
If you succeed you can pick another greater ability you qualify for. A feat only three can claim through out the history of Atresus

objects.title: Madness
objects.text:
Your mind will betray you . It starts as a voice, quiet and gentle at first. In the beginning, it will start as a helpful mentor, but slowly it will ask you to commit acts against your moral alignment. In the beginning it will show you new ways to use your gifts, and secrets not even you with years of training could have figured out. You will grow so much faster than if you had by yourself. However with every trick and technique it shows you it will ask something of you. The acts will be small and nothing you will bat an eye to at first. But the more you deny the voice and ignore it requests. The more violent and loud it becomes. This doesn’t sound like a drawback until your third saga. By then the voice will have calmed and disappeared. Or so you thought no the voice has implanted itself deep within your thoughts. Now you cannot tell what thoughts are yours and which are its. You can no longer trust your own mind. The only way to rid yourself of this is to tear it out. However, this comes at a cost not only is finding a mage gifted enough to do this without killing you will take at least one saga. But even then the thing is now a part of you. Removing it will take a piece of you. Your mind will be slower, whatever gifts it granted you are gone. Your skills are duller and your memories foggy. 
There is a companion who can somewhat heal you If you successfully complete their loyalty mission.

objects.title: Hesitance
objects.text:
You are weak, you are a failure, you are a waste. Yours is the opposite of will. You hesitate when others fly. At a basic level, this drawback makes it so that you are more agreeable in general. You take on minor quests more often. 
If you were fool enough to pick magik with this drawback then your magiks will sometimes fail. Refusing to be wielded by one who lacks the will to act and force their truth upon the world. Once every full moon your sorceries will act on their own accord. Creating something beyond your understanding and seeing. Each time your magiks will grow weaker, more stunted. The well you drew on becoming shallower.  Till one day it completely disappears, you will be empty. As though a part of you was roughly curved out leaving, you hollow. You can no longer wield magiks. One day you will need to find where it went. (saga)

If you didn’t take sorceries, then you are more susceptible to mind magiks. One day you will meet a stranger. They will only approach you when none of your companions are near and take you away. You will find yourself entrapped by the stranger. It will start out small, a smile that catches your fancy a touch that sends shivers up your spine and a kiss that will leave you breathless. Twice every month they will appear and whisk you away. You will never tell your companions of what happened or where you go. For even you can't remember. Though each time you will be left with a sense of satisfaction. And a feeling of that lingering kiss. 
After six encounters you will start having holes in your memory. Though you do not know what happened you will sometimes get flashbacks at inopportune times. Or after you regain consciousness, you will find your hands bloodied and with a heart-shaped kiss of crimson on your chest. Even then you will still yearn for the stranger’s presence, you will still thirst for the stranger's kiss. An ache will fill you that not even your life partner can fill. Though a part of you, thats quiet and small. A part of you that was beaten suppressed and hidden will know that something is VERY wrong. You will do everything in your power to suppress that part. 
One day the stranger will disappear leaving you alone. You will suffer a pain greater than heartbreak, you will grow withdrawn and hollow. Your nights will be filled with tears, and your days will be filled with raging and raving. You will drink and fight at every opportunity, hoping to forget or find that which was lost. This will cause a divide between you and your companions.
One day you will have to face what you did with that stranger.

objects.title: Warrgghh!
objects.text: Your berserker rage is poisoned. Instead of feeling the rage during battles, you feel it outside of it. If someone mistakes your order you are likely to destroy it, the tavern and a few blocks around it for the mistake. Your rages will be for stupid, petty and childish reasons. However, the moment a battle begins the rage leaves you, making you a bumbling idiot. What’s more your strength, speed and intelligence will be halved for an equal amount of time, relative to how long you raged. Your strength and speed are quadrupled instead of the usual doubled. Making you twice as strong as any average berserker. Though finding a reason to rage, during battle is hard. Even if your companions were injured during battle it will take a serious wound for the rage to rise. And even then its potency will be low.

objects.title: See no evil
objects.text:
Your sight will betray you. You will see things that aren’t and sometimes things that are there but no other than you can see. This will sometimes save your life, though telling the difference between the two will be nigh impossible. By your third saga you will no longer sleep. These sights can still be seen even when you cover/close your eyes. Telling reality from fiction through your sight will become impossible. Sometimes you will see companions though they will have no recollection of meeting you. Sometimes one thing will become another, food will look rotten and maggot-infested even though it is fine. The effects will vary but you will not go a day without seeing this. As time passes the things you see will grow in horror and truth. You will see things mortal eyes weren't meant to see, remember some things were meant to be hidden. By your sixth saga, you will see the one thing that causes the celestial dragons to flee from the idea of flesh. You will no longer be the same. You will bare witness to the one thing that even the great scions of magik and runes could not bare to see. The crimson will forsake you. Your death will come soon after. 
The only way to truly be rid of them. Is to blind yourself. Healing your eyes will return the visions.

objects.title: Hear no evil
objects.text:
Your ears will betray you. You will hear things others cannot. At first, you will be able to tell a lie from just the tone of someone’s voice. You will be able to tell the number of people in a room from their heartbeats. As time passes you will start to hear a voice. The voice will be of your preference. Almost made perfectly for you, in a way that you cannot do anything but listen. This voice will guide you, it will tell you of dangers just before they affect you. Poison in your wine the voice will tell you what the poison is but not who poisoned you. By your second saga, the voice will be almost prophetic. Telling you of things yet to be. Sometimes the voice will guide you to opportune times, which are favourable to you. You will find long-lost treasures and artifacts that will make you and your companions much stronger. 
Taking a heated blade to the ears is the only answer. You will be deaf. Healing this returns the voice. It will have missed you.

objects.title: Speak no evil
objects.text:
Your lips will betray you. Your word is law. Depending on your social standing or authority people become agreeable. When you want them to, they will genuinely do as you ask. For example, if you are a warrior and claim someone is your enemy. People will believe them to be so, they will be hostile to the person. The higher your standing is the more potent your voice is. Though if your will is greater than others you can command them. However, those with a strong enough willpower can ignore your voice. 
With this ability, climbing rising through the ranks will not be difficult especially if you have the skills for it. A warrior becoming the general of a nation will be simple. A farmer becoming an emperor will take decades. Though if you have the foresight and cunning the time can be halved. 
If you were a king, your word would quite literally be law. Even if you personally didn’t tell someone to do something. As long as enough people hear your words, it will spread. You have enough control over this ability that you can’t accidentally tell someone to hurt themselves and they hurt themselves. You must want it to happen for it to happen. However, you must be specific you cannot look at a tree and tell it to fall. No, you must tell someone to cut the tree down. As long as someone is capable of doing something they will do it to the best of their ability. 

Destroying your vocal cords or removing your own tongue are the only ways to be rid of this.

objects.title: Do no evil
objects.text:
Attacks made on your person will be returned twice over on the one who attacked. You even something such as being hit by a collapsed build will have the forces transferred onto the person who attacked you. This also works for magikal attacks and even hexes or curses. You may walk through a battlefield and have an army bring itself to ruin by trying to attack you. You do not need to see or even feel the attack for this effect to take place. Its as though something watches over you, waiting for a fool to attack. 
Alternatively, you can mark your allies with these abilities. Making them just like you though instead of twice over the effect would be equal for them. You can mark others though the effect is not as strong for them, nor does it last as long. 

Driving red hot nails into your flesh is the only way to stop this. Removing them will return the effect.

rows.title: Truth
rows.titleText:
What is it child of crimson that you wish for?
Everything in this land can kill you, even the kiss of a lover held dear can hide a dagger between them. So child who the crimson beckons for. What is it that you want? Do you want riches and adoration? Do you want to collapse kingdoms? Or do you want to it the lands in blood and gore? 
Do you desire peace? Or maybe you’d like to carve out a piece of Atresus that is yours and yours alone? A land where neighbour can greet neighbour without fear of a knife to the belly. 
Or do you simply wish to explore? To wander from place to place finding wonder and beauty, seeing sights only you can witness till your hairs are bleached from the sun and your skin is tanned? 
Let me tell you this now child of metal, of fire, lightning, and terrible dark destiny. The Crimson cares not for your wishes, it cares not for what you wish to achieve, for what you wish to claim or how so you wish to claim it. All that matters and all that is true to the Crimson is strength. Not just physical or metaphysical might, nor just mental or emotional. No… the crimson cares for one thing and one thing alone. TRUE STRENGTH. The strength which burns within you. 
Whether you have the strength to bleed for what you believe in. The strength to live with the consequences of your actions. All that matters in the crimson is thine strength of person and identity. All else is sand upon the wind. Prove that your beliefs are better, prove that your wishes should be held above others, and prove that you are worthy of your blood. Prove that you are worthy crimson.

rows.title: Early Life events(WIP)
rows.titleText: What life events shaped you crimson? What led you to meet your companions? What made you rise above your rivals? Who were your enemies? What broke or healed you? Who taught you? Who did you love? How many did you leave behind? Tell me, child of the red, what made you?

objects.title: Choice
objects.text:
During one of your adventures, you stopped by a port city. As your companions went about replenishing supplies, you wandered the streets. There you met a wisened old man. He spoke in riddles and lost tongues. 
Very few paid the old man mind and the few that did, gave him looks of pitty as they sleep coppers into his cup. 
You asked the guard who the man was, and they replied with a shake of their heads. Saying he was a crazy man who'd been year since they were little boys. 
The sun was hot that day, in a stroke of compassion you bought him an umbrella and a cool drink. 
The man's cloudy eyes turned to you and he spoke. Words fell from his lips as with such a weight that you fell back. 
You could have turned and left, your good deed for the day done. But instead, you listened. Then and there the man told you of a saga yet to be lived of a decision yet to be made. 
He spoke with such clarity and lucidity that you knew his words to be true. 
As the final words dripped from his lips the man vanished umbrella and all. 
Leaving you alone and confused in the streets. When you asked the nearby guards, they had no recollection of who you spoke of. 
Stunned you left the street soon after, with an idea of a possible future yet to be set in stone. 
What was it the man told you?

objects.title: Choice
objects.text: It was a day unlike any other, you made camp. You were first on watch duty. But for some reason you a deep slumber overcame you. In your dreams, you travelled yo a realm far from here. One that felt alien to your dreamself. In this realm could be he

objects.title: Seal of Confrontation
objects.text:
It started as mere challegne. Something simple, something on a normal day you wouldn't have butted an eye to. On that day you suffered your first loss. It had been nothing you'd felt like before. As they looked at you, their eyes were live with victory and accomplishment. They did not pity you, they did not look down on you. They did not gloat, they only looked at you an eyebrow arched. A silent question is another challenge. 

"Is that all?"

From that day onwards they become your rival. Every day you strived to be better than them, you trained, you studied, and you learnt. 

A fire was ignited in you. 

Every opportunity you had you challenged them. For years you tested your mettle against theirs. Sometimes you'd win, but more often than not you'd lose. Always their eyes would ask the same question. 

One day there was something in the air, as though a single spark would set the town aflame. You don't know how or why but you found each other. Both of you knew this would be your last fight for some time. 

It took all that you had and even then it seemed like it wouldn't be enough, you would loose. The moment the idea crossed your mind the fire in your belly grew into a bonfire consuming whatever doubts you had, as though the very idea of another loss was an afront to your very soul. You won by the skin of your teeth, earning both their respect and friendship.

Your journey demanded you leave. Did you take them with you or did you leave them?

objects.title: seal of Reconciliation
objects.text: You reached out a hand, your eyes asked the question yet your mouth remained silent. The smiled reaching up and taking your hand. They joined you. Pick a rival to take as a companion.

objects.title: Goodbye
objects.text:
You did not reach out, you did not ask. This chapter of your life was over. Now your journey truly begun. 
They offered you a memento to remember them by. Take an extra item

objects.title: Into the woods
objects.text:
You were but a child playing in the woods, you had wandered too far and now were lost to the forest. You searched and searched trying to find your way back. But as the hours passed, you found no salvation. Hunger gnawed at your insides and thirst robbed the moisture from your lips. Which lay cracked and bleeding. 

WInter had just arrived, robbing the trees of their leaves and your body of its warmth. Still, by some grace you had worn a jacket. So at least you will not be freezing to death, at least not yet. 

Like any child feeling alone and lost you wept, great deep sobs heaved themselves from deep inside. Believing this to be your last day, you cried till there was no more left. 
It was then you heard a mewling more wretched than your own. 

What did you do?

objects.title: It came from the woods.
objects.text:
Your feet carried you forward long before you knew why. 

Maybe it was due to the pity you felt for whatever creature made those sounds or maybe it was the idea that you wouldn't have to be alone. 

It was there in the middle of the clearing when you happened upon them. Two creatures, unlike anything you'd seen before. They lay broken and dead, deep cushes that poured dark blood, leaked from the wounds across their bodies. 

Behind one of the creatures came the crying you heard, this time weaker. As you approached the fear you should have felt before blossomed. 

What if this was a trick? What id whatever was behind there came out to eat you?

All those thoughts vanished, as your eyes landed on a tine wounded form. It lay next to the dead creature. It cries growing weaker and weaker as it nudged at what you now understand to be its mother. Which must have died defending it cub. 

By now the child had set it, a light snow fell, coating the corpses and freezing there blood. The coat you wore was no longer warm enough.

Opening your coat you picked up the cub and pressed it against your body. Sharing what little warmth you had left with it. 

The crying had stopped you weren't sure if it was a good or bad thing. As the cold set into your bones and your eyelids grew heavy. You closed them at peace with the fact that you wouldn't be alone.

You awoke to a warmth against your chest. Opening your eyes you stared up at a familiar ceiling with an unfamiliar guest in your room. It was the cub, a soft purr terminating from its chest. 

From then on the cub has been with you growing as you do.

objects.title: Choice
objects.text:
You ignored the tears instead, you wiped your own. You refused to give up. Instead, you collected whatever little firewood you could find and started a fire. 
There you sat waiting, even as the snow fell and tears froze you waited. 
Hours passed as the strange melted from your body and a stiffness filled your limbs. 
It was then they found you, the fire had died a long time ago. 
They wrapped you up in furs and carried you back to your hometown.

objects.title: Choice
objects.text:
It was in the way they smiled at you, in the way they looked at you. You knew from that moment on they'd claimed you. It took every ounce of strength not to fall into their arms when they approached you.
From then on your days were filled with joys unlike anything you'd felt before. Their kiss was sweeter than any honey, and more intoxicating than the finest of wines. 
So when you had that someone had taken them, an unholy rage filled you. 
By then you only had two of your lesser abilities and those who stole her from you were vile sorcerers, those in your village told you to give up and that these things happen. 
Those were only served to stock the flames. 
 
What did you do?

objects.title: Choice
objects.text:
The only thing you could, you went and found them. It wasn't hard it was though an invisible hand guided you fourth tell you where to go. It took you two days to find them. You would've waited biding your time until you heard the opportune time to strike. That was until you saw your lover.
You were a few ways away, still, you could see them. The sight of them filled you with RAGE. They had been beaten, there clothes torn. 
There eyes locked onto you as silent plea, telling you to turn back to leave.

objects.title: Sable the crimson witch
objects.text:
“Let those in-between taste your blood”
Sable is a witch from a tribe of crimson warlocks who use a hidden technique. That is most definitely forbidden. They use blood to power their dreaded magiks. The can control the blood in their bodies, causing it to multiple, harden and purge poisons. They can eject it from their body to form constructs and other things. Sable is also batshit crazy due to a ritual that was forced upon her in her youth. They bathed her in the blood of a newborn dragon. Of course the dragons parent wasn’t to happy to hear their brood was used for some ritual. Destroy every last practitioner of the dreaded art. Being extremely powerful at this point Sable couldn’t have stopped the bloodshed. She didn’t only stepping in when the dragon attacked her. She latter repeated the ritual 
+Powerful able to use her magiks to heal you and your companions to full health. Even going so far as restoring lost limbs. 
+Makes a mean cherry pie
+/-Dragons are afraid off her will either avoid your group or go out of their way to burn everything within a mile of her. Which consequently means you and your companions.  
-Rarely will heal anyone and if she does will laud it over whoever she healed for weeks on end. 
-Is needlessly cruel, can and will torture for fun
-Is slowly going mad with each passing day due to the dragon’s blood. Will one day loose control turning into some blood dragon hybrid that will be incredibly difficult to put down. 
-If offer to do the same ritual for you or your companions DECLINE. It will be excruciatingly painful. Not because of the dragon’s blood burning through your veins. But the truth it opens your mind to.
- After going full dragon, if any of your companions are bathed in her blood. You will be turned into a lesser draken. I mindless slave as the blood constantly consume you from within until you fall apart. It could take days, weeks, months or years. 
-If not taken as a companion this will become a future saga you can pick to deal with.

objects.title: Gnasher the green lion
objects.text:
“Ey boss, notin like der smell of sulfur to get yer up in der mornin”
Left his tribe cause he got tired of having to experiment his new potions on the Rattling’s. Is manic and is constantly moving, either tapping his toes or juggling beakers full of volatile concoctions. Can tell the funniest jokes. Many jokes are crude and can come of a somewhat ignorant. Has ten siblings, which is considered little in the goblen community. Will kill anyone who gives them trouble. 
+ He’s pretty chill by goblen standards meaning he’ll only attempt to knife you in the back if he thinks your going soft.
+Can make healing reagents but complains every time he has to. Claiming his skill is wasted on them.
+Can make powerful poisons and explosive. Though you’ll have to use them away from the rest of the crew. Because most of his experiments tend to backfire on the one who uses it. 
+/- Insists on calling you boss. Not because he thinks your boss but because he thinks your name is stupid. 
+/- Is a walking alchemy lab if you have the alchemist perk. You can both create the potion you need for the chronic illness drawback to about a few hours. In a few years, you could even cure it. It will cost you to make though. 
- Is a walking alchemy lab could blow up and level a few blocks if the wrong reagents are mixed.  
-Cackles in his sleep when he has one of those ‘dreams’. Its much worse than snoring. Expect to lose sleep for the first few days of adventuring with him.

objects.title: Husher the Everrotten
objects.text:
Also known as husher the unwashed, suflurpits, vilestench. And on and on his name go. If you pick hum, you’ll never find an assassin as loyal as husher. His steps are quiets his dagger sharp and his poisons harsh. Since he was a wee little goblen he had trained to be the greatest assassin. You will smell him long before you see him. Like seriously the smoke in the picture isn’t smoke. Its his musk. Will call it his ‘aura’. It isn’t, it really isn’t. Claims that a witch cursed him, saying if he ever washed, he would loose his sense if self. Funny thing is he wasn’t actually cursed at least not magically. It wasn’t even a real witch who ‘cursed him’. Just some random old hug who didn’t like Husher. That didn’t stop him from believing he was cursed and hasn’t washed since. 
+Honestly one of the best assassins.
+Steps are as silent as the wind.
+Can teach you to blend in with shadows and crowded streets.
+Makes better potions than any alchemist. 
+Gives great life advice.
-Can be smelt for miles
-Truly smells horrendous
-Will take a long time to convince him he’s not genuinely cursed.
-Only knows a handful of antidotes.

objects.title: Alabaster Sword Seeks Atonement Through Victory
objects.text:
““
This is not good Assattv shouldn’t be here, its an impossibility. The celestial elves should be locked away trapped against their eternal struggle with the quantum dragons. The powerful and eternal dragons you see on our world are nothing compared to the true gods that prowl the far reaches universe. Makers of suns and worlds your mind cannot hope to comprehend. If Assatty is here then the implications are dire. No one knows its reason for being here. It is bound to you and that is never a good thing. 
The crimson in your veins stirs…in an almost pleased manner.
-Completely alien, his voice will break lesser minds.
+Powerful can travel through dreams.
-Hasn’t had a body for a long time, will need time to acclimate. Could take hours, days, weeks or even months.
+/- Concept of helping may need some work. Would cut of your arm if you ever used it to hurt you or anyone you care about.

objects.title: Zafir
objects.text:
You met Zafir within the Djinn-infested deserts. At the time he claimed to be a humble man who ran a local brothel. After a group of thugs attempted to harm one of his workers, you intervened saving her life. Zafir invited you back to his establishment. Where he offered you the finest food drink and company that night. Once you had your fill of whatever you accepted Zafir offered you a job. You see Zafir is one of the greatest spymaster of the region. He uses a network of brothels to collect information and sell it for a great sum. Zafir offered you his services if you 'took care' of the thieves' guild that had begun infesting the city. How you did was up to you. 
Since that day Zafir has been selling you information at a fraction of its cots.
+Will get you hard-to-find information
+Can warn you in advance if someone is looking for you. 
+Half of the brothels in Actar become safehavens for you and you group.
+/- Half djinn
-/+His fire magic is just an illusion
-Lies as easily as he breaths, except when it comes to the information he sells.
+/- Often flirts and openly tries to seduce you. Though he will never let it go anywhere.

objects.title: Oldman Logan
objects.text:
An adventurer who has seen many battles and has fought almost every beast within the western side of Astesus at least twice. Has a large family he enjoys visiting and telling tales of his adventures. 
An encyclopedia of endemic wild life as well as multiple ways to hunt and butcher wild beasts. 
His adventuring days are over, though is a well of important information. 
+Will take you to visit his family. This will rejuvenate and calm the soul. They will treat you with kindness.
+Gives great grandfatherly advice.
+Will make animal encounters easier. 
+Can make certain encounters/Saga only half as difficult. 
+Will make you and your team more efficient and coordinated. 
-Has a minor version of the chronic pains drawbacks. Some days the pace of your travels will slow considerably. 
-Constantly talks about Aisha his lost love. She wanted to settle and they tried to but Logan couldn't. His thirst for adventure is too great.
-Refuses to stay in the same place for more than a few months. 
+Is well known amongst adventurers.

objects.title: Jack Moonshine
objects.text:
If a djinn lives long enough it can gain the intelligence of a human. Mixed with their already present shapeshifting abilities. Some Djinns can choose to live in any society without being noticed. 
Jack isn't one of these. She is a half djinn. Who inherited more of her mother's genetics without the inherit shapeshifting abilities. Making fitting into society somewhat difficult for her. She does not care for this and openly flaunts her heritage. 
Within Actar Jack has become somewhat of an icon if not a living legend. She prowls the desert, fighting off great sand wyrms and protecting the caravan earning her some goodwill. 
However, this alone doesn't make up for Jacks notorious legend. Jack is known as the ender of great bloodlines. 
Jack has single-handedly ending three great house bloodlines for she seduced half of the heirs. Who after a night with Jack refuses any suitors thereafter and repeatedly attempts to escape their house to search for Jack. 
Of course, this isn't due to any magics, Jack is just that good.
+A powerhouse in her own right, though in more of tank. 
+Can teach you a thing or two about sedcution and pleasing a partner.
+/-Depending on who you meet will either be regarded as a folk hero or a wanted criminal. 
+/-Both her suitors and their parents are searching for Jack. Depending on how you use this, it could either be an advantage or disadvantage. 
-Terrified of settling down or getting into a monogamous relationship.
+Cooks the best spicey food.
+Will get you discounts from merchants. 
-Constalty has to be on the move if you are in Actar
-Encounters with assassins will become common in any desert. 
-Wild djinn seem almost drawn to her.

objects.title: Menso collector of stories.
objects.text:
Menso is a tavern owner and bartender with a pension for getting whatever goods you require as long as you have the gold for it. Will give you a large discount if you tell him a great tale. 
+Friendly has a way of disarming even the meanest veterans. And could quite literally wring a story from a stone.
-Very hard to hide information from him if you really want to get it from him. 
+What you tell him is told in confidence. 
+Will help you find the most obscure treasure sights.
+Knows just the right drink to pour for you.
+Makes the best ciders and ales. 
-Can read you as easily as one can read a book. 
-Information can be sometimes expensive. 
-Will not give information on his other clients.

objects.title: Oud
objects.text:
Not much is known about Oud. The shadows seem to lick and curl at their feet. Known as the lone traveler. Not once was Oud seen travelling with another person. That was until they met you. From the moment you met Oud has not left your side. Following you throughout all your adventures. At first you found their constant presence somewhat odd. Especially from the fact they never spoke. Though their body hands and feet would move somewhat randomly at times. But as time moved on you found comfort in their company. Oud was a master of the shadows able to command them as extra limbs or to store objects. In battle, Oud is a shifting mass of dark spikey tendrils each holding a different weapon. From club to spear to sword and crossbow. After weeks together you soon learnt that the movements and twitching of Ouds body weren't a random effect but their way of communicating. After months of study and learning you were finally able to understand Oud. 
+Is a literal demon in battle able to multitask and attack multiple opponents at once.
+Can use their shadows to store your goods and weapons. 
+Is highly mobile when using their tendrils.
-Rarely speaks.
-Is somewhat of a loner. 
-Nights are darker and shadows are longer when Oud is around.

objects.title: Aisha
objects.text:
Aisha currently runs an adventurer's guild while training new recruits. She is also the former lover of Logan.  One of the greatest spear users in the whole nation and could train you in the use of it. Is a charming and charismatic woman. Makes great company. 
+Will make you one of the greatest spear user on the continent if you agree yo train with her for four years. One if you are a wepaonsmaster. 
+Will provide you with the best quests and rewards if you and your companions agree to go on training missions with some of her recruits. 
+Great person to share drinks with. Will help you heal from some of the dark shit you've seen.
-Constantly worries for her son and will always ask for you to keep an eye on him.
-If you travel Njoroge, Aisha will insist on joining you. Njoroge will leave if you agree. 
-Will get bitter and mean if someone mentions Logans name.
-Will initially be hostile with you and you group if Logan is in it.

objects.title: Njoroge
objects.text:
The son of Aisha and Logan. A sword master in his own right. He inherited both his father's sharp memory and his mother's skills. As well as both of their personality traits. Will act as the emotional support for your group. Is an outgoing fellow always pushing to improve himself. Knows many of the adventers on a first name basis.
+Tells the best campfire stories.
+Is skilled with the sword.
+Can make the best out of any situation.
+Will push you and your companions to train and improve with him.
+An natural born leader. If leader you will find your fame growing as well as your skill. 
-If your are the leader will fight you for the right to lead. Not because of any malice but because he truly believes himself to be best suited for the job.
+If able to prove that you are the better leader. You will find in him a loyal and steadfast second in command. Following even your vaguest of orders and bringing the best out of them.
-Sometimes pushes himself and your group too far when it comes to training. Though will be easy to rear him down if you have proven yourself.
-Has a poor relationship with his father, and will kick him out fo the group if he part of your crew. If not he will leave himself. 
-Avoid his mother like the plague. Making getting information or training from her difficult.

objects.title: Ogun the Bulwark of Machakos
objects.text:
Ogun the bulwork of machakos. Contrary to his looks Ogun plays more of a support role than as a warrior. He mainly focuses on buffs and debufs. He was once known as the greatest supporter and had whole adventure guilds begging him to join them.  
Ogun got his name from an adventure of his. Where he used every single buff and debuff to his name against and army of three hundred. A feet thought impossible for a support role. 
For three nights and four days, Ogun held a single narrow mountain pass as the women and children of his hometown were evacuated. 
Though he was able to hold them off until his peoples allies arrived it came at a grave cost. 
By the end of your sagas, Ogun is guaranteed to die. His body has come to rely on the buffs he constantly feeds it. Without it, his bones will collapse under the weight of his muscles. His organs crushed and his skin torn.
+/- Buffs and debuffs are only half as effective since he uses the remaining on himself. 
+Buffs/skills are still a cut above the rest. 
+Cooks the healthiest and most nutritious meals that will leave you refreshed and energised. 
-Need to be defended during fights.
-Hates elfens with a passion. Will not travel with you if you or your companions are elfen. 
-Might kill you and your companions if either of you are elfen.

objects.title: Grevin
objects.text:
Grevin an undead litch. One of the best magik users on the continent. Was once hailed as the second coming of Ottar the foul. Had planned a rebellion, starting his own dark religion and spreading magic amongst his country men. Which was considered a great tabboo. A war so great almost brought the downfall of his people. After winning Grevin surrendered the throne and spent many lifetimes rebuilding his home and his people. Banning magik once more.But that was all in his youth. Now he is a husk of a man, full of regret and sorrow. Wishes to to do something right with the remainder of his life. Has three daughters two of which he abandoned with their mothers. Believing he would only hurt them if he stayed to raise them. 
+Mastered curses and hexes
+Will show you long-forgotten magiks if you have a knack for them.
+Is a fierce warrior and can train you to be even greater.
-Has grown tired of fighting and will never do so.
-Is a serious vibe kill.

objects.title: Karana Allender
objects.text:
Karana is the eldest sister and daughter of Grevin. Karana from birth was trained in nothing but war by her mother. Learning everything from leadership to guerilla tactics to single combat. Her mother had hopes of using her as a weapon to accomplish what her father failed to do long ago. She never had time to do anything but fight and thus struggles with anything not related to war. A warrior first a person second.  Hates her mother and father and is jealous of her sister Kinami who was raised by her father. She always dreamt of her father coming to rescue her from her mother but he never did.
+Is a weapons master in her own right. 
+Can fight a whole army with nothing but cowards and thieves and still wind up on top. Though with serious casualties. 
+Is an edge lord to the max. Says stuff like "Oh death be my sword once more"
-Can be cruel to companions.
-Is somewhat of a sadist.
+Underneath all the cruelty and self-loathing is a woman who has never known love and has been treated as nothing but a weapon for most of her life.
+If you can help her face her traumas, she will become your most passionate warrior and or lover. 
-Has spilt more blood than you can imagine.
-Is plagued by nightmares of her past actions. 
-If not helped will turn to alcohol and drugs as a coping mechanism.

objects.title: Narrak
objects.text:
Narrak is a rogue and a bard. Able to charm the pants of off almost anyone. Hell, most will offer their shirts too if they could. Fun-loving and will bring an air of lightheartedness throughout most of your adventures. Will never talk about her self. 
+Has a kick that could dent armour.
+Plays almost every instrument. 
+Will southe you and your companions after long journey. 
-Is a cleptomaniac who will constantly steal things from you, your group, townfolks and almost anyone in her near vicinity. 
-This can bring about unwanted attention and create tension within your group.

objects.title: Monolith
objects.text:
Monolith is a creation of the old ones. A golem made of a mixture of metal and stone. Monolith is a quiet defender, and known as the defender of the weak. WOuld move from town to town village to village defending them from monster attacks. He would settle for a year before moving on. The cloth and jewellery covering him were gifts given to him by those he defended.  One day he helped you defeat and thunder bird terrorizing a small town. After a year he found you and has stuck with you since. A master earth elemental. 
+Can move boulders the size of houses with ease.
+Can learn some intricacies of earth magic if you are magickly inclined.
+Villages and towns it saved will hail you as a hero, giving you discounts and free lodging and meals.
+/- Will not ally with you if you harm the weak. May kill you if you do. 
+/-Very difficult to put down.
+Cannot speak.
-Is very heavy and moves slowly. 
-Has trouble entering normal buildings or houses. 
-Will follow your orders to the letter. You need to be very specific.
-Need to recharge once every year. It is highly vulnerable.

objects.title: Kisari
objects.text:
Kisari the second eldest sister. Also known as the death of silence. One of the greatest assassins of the elfen empire. Trained by the oldest of masters to be the fiercest blade to the throne. As her final test, she was ordered to kill them. The same people who raised and trained her. 
Unlike her eldest sister, she enjoyed it. Is the current assassin to the elfen queen, Karanas mother. Who owns her leash. 
+Femme fatale personality.
+A fantastic actor and can disguise herself as almost anyone. 
+Her steps are so silent and light to the point that she can use leaves as stepping stones. 
+None can hear her approach. 
-Enjoys killing.
-Takes her time in killing her enemies. 
-Has murdered more people than her two sisters combined. 
-Will oneday kill her sisters and father. For no other reason other than to test herself. 
+/- Can be stopped as long as you can prove to be worthy of holding her leash.

objects.title: CHCHCHC
objects.text:
Named after the sounds she makes when she's pleased. No one knows what she actually is. She was found in the basement of Wizards Tower, which for some reason or another just disappeared. Leaving a basement of horrors and an interdimensional portal the local militia with the help of you and your companiosn. Upon defeating monster horde after monster horde eldritch horror. All that was left behind was her. Of course you chose to do the most reasonable thing and adopt her. Eats anything an everything though for some reason she prefers warm-blooded animals. 
+Is one of the few creatures that can contend with the celerity blessing.
+Loyal 
+Can track anything as long as its on the same continent
+Has the intelligence of a somewhat intelligent bloodhound. 
+Claws can tear through armor
-Vicous to strangers.
-Overheats after running to much. 
-Doesn't do well in cold climates.
-If left to her own devices will hunt the local wildlife to extinction.

objects.title: Choice
objects.text:
+Carries insane and powerful technology within it. Could take on an army solo.
+Can forge any melee weapon you could imagine at of almost anything. 
+Will keep your equipment in peak condition 
+Dissapears for weeks at a time, fulfilling some unknown directive. 
-Speaks through whirs and clicks. 
-Watches what you and your team does. 
-Sometimes in the middle of the night, you will find it stark still. Staring up and into the sky as a blue light envelops it. The clicks it will make will be clearer and almost legible. Do not let it catch you. 

DO NOT 01110100 01110010 01110101 01110011 01110100 00100000 01101001 01110100 00001010

objects.title: Fangna
objects.text: 'Don't look her in the eyes.' Is a phrase you'll often hear when is near. A 9ft tower of rippling muscle and razor sharp tusks. Fangna is one of the few orcs you'll see miles away from the borders. Orphaned at a young age, she was raised by a infamous mercenary group. Who knew nothing about raising an ork. So in the end the only thing she did learn from them was might makes right.

rows.title: Life partner
rows.titleText: Life partners.

objects.title: Sera Flaimehaired
objects.text:
“Aw man you should have seen the Goreki springs, there crystal-clear water were like the ambrosia of the gods. One sip and my woes and trouble melted away like the morning dew. Too bad the spring guardian did not appreciate that.”
Hailing from the lands of the east, where she knows only of the border wars with the mintori. From the moment she could properly walk her father put an axe in her hand and told her to go and claim the emerald fields. For years she fought against the mintori. At first, she enjoyed the journey and fighting, but after a few years of seeing the same landscape she started hating every moment of it. Seeing the same battles, fighting the same opponents and going home to the same place was hel. It did nothing to sate the wanderlust brewing in her heart. So, the moment she had the opportunity to leave she left. 
+Great with the axe, like ridiculously so. Could fell a boulder with a flick of the wrist.
+Romance is easy if you share her wanderlust. If you don’t well…
+Well-travelled. She will regale you off stories from her travels.
+/- Never stops talking about how much she loves travelling. 
+/- Will hate is if you stay in the same place for more than a few months.
-Will leave the group if her wanderlust isn’t satiated. 
-They search for something, could be a lover, could be a home, could be a treasure. Stick with them and they might know. 
-Can get bored easily.

objects.text:
Nothing much is know about Groko. Tales of a masked warlock popped. He would slay beasts with his dreaded magiks and runes. Would wonder searching for anything strong that threatened people. Is good with kids and a friendly guy all around. Don’t ask about his mask, don’t touch his mask. Travels with his twin sister. 
+Will teach you things about magik and runes you did not know about.
+Is pleasant to be around, great listener. 
+Is welcome around most towns.(townsfolk will be friendly if Gorok is with you. Expect discounts.
- Must take him with his sister if taken as a companion and not a life partner. 
+ Can have both twins as life partners if Krogo deems you worthy. 
-Never takes his mask off. 
-if his mask is removed the world will end. (Pandora’s box type situation) 
-No seriously don’t touch his mask if you don’t want to fuck everything up for everyone.
- Is lactose intolerant.
- Flinches at physical
-barefoot heathen.

objects.title: Kendasa Rugdur
objects.text:
“…Never again.”
Kendassa is from an isolationist tribe of orcs. Trained in shamanism and nature magiks. Communing with the nature father. In her tribes when one proposes they give a collar to their partner. It is an intimate gesture one of trust and vulnerability. It is a claim you trust another with all you are, with all you hope to be. She lived a good life and dreamed of the day she would marry someone worthy. Someone who would love her thoroughly, someone to be her “alterum dimidium”. Raiders found her home Pillaging and taking. Many were taken and even more were killed. The last memory Keesan has of her beautiful home, was it burning in green flames. The bodies of her sisters and brothers strewn about after being used. She was chained, and brought into a life of slavery by a mad mage who bought her. The mage learnt of her traditions and made of mockery of them. She made a iron collar, made of metal that stay cold to the touch. The collar was made with magical properties that connected the two. Now they were bonded, what the mage felt Kenassa could and what Kenassa could feel the mage could as well. Though the mad mages was more one way, she had more control over it. 
Using the collar the mage would perfume perverse and obscene acts upon Kenassa. The mage was a masochist enjoying the pain and sensations inflicted on both of them. For years Kenassa put uf with this until one day she snapped. All that was left was brier incased mages toward and a corpse surrounded in thorns that bore into its flesh. A metal collar around its necks. 
-Mean as hell
-Isolationist prefers to be by herself. Will tend to stay away from other in the crew. 
+Powerful nature magiks.
-If your hand ever goes near her without permission, you will lose both it and the other one. 
+Great healer. Like one of the best.

objects.title: Ishkar
objects.text:
Ishkar is one of the lesser-known races from beyond the blighted lands. No one knows who she is or how she got here. Not even Ishkar herself. All she remembers is following bloody footprints and a warm presence leading her through the wastes and urging her on. Orcs from the fringes weren’t sure what to do when they found a little girl at the edge of the borderland. Untouched and unscathed. With faded bloody footprints too big to be hers trailing into the waste. Any that followed them never returned. The orcs raised her as best as they could teaching her honour and ferocity. Since she had no blood of ifnar Breachbinder flowing through her veins. She wasn’t bound to the land nor did she have the honour of protecting it. Once she was of age she left the lands wandering and learning.
Ishkar is a calm and collected individual. She speaks but often prefers to listen. Though when she has something on her mind she doesn’t fear bringing it up. She is a proud and strong warrior. He fists akin to still. Some believe she was blessed with strength. Though she was loved and treated with respect Ishkar has always felt like an outsider. Because of this, she hasn’t been in a relationship. To the border orcs, a relationship is Akin to settling down. And none wanted to settle down with one not bound to the land. It will take some time for her to open up to you. But when she does expect to be met with a hungry passion that stems from being touch starved. 
+Can keep a cool head in the harshest of times
+Her fists hit like three orcs combined
+Can train you in hand-to-hand combat.
+An almost encyclopaedic memory. 
-Distrusts magik and any magik user
-Can be ruthless in battle
-When drunk the idea of personal space is foreign to her.
-Is obsessed with finding the origin of the footprints. Will obsessively search for and collect any information on the footprint. Can be expensive and time-consuming. Expects you to help foot the bill. (make a quest)

objects.title: Krogo Maskfiend
objects.text:
Twin sister to Groko. Also wears a mask though their power is tied to it. Face beneath the mask appears to be an abyss. Terrible to look at and will cause nightmares for days if you look into the one golden eye in the middle of her face. Where Groko is kind Krogo is an ass. Will actively work against you until you prove to be worthy standing next to her brother. How you go about this is up to you. Be careful. 
+/-Total ass until they respect you. Then they will kill anyone who looks at you wrong
+Is ridiculously strong can summon defeated foes using shadowy summons from their mask. 
+/- Can create new summons from defeat foes. Though they have to be beasts and not people. 
+/- Romance is incredibly difficult even after proving yourself. Will constantly question if you care about them. Avoid any flirting like the plague.
+/- Must take with their brother. 
-Like a total ass, will sometimes remove the mask just to give you nightmares.
- Is snappy and rude.
-Has to eat defeated foes so as to summon them. DO NOT WATCH. The sounds are enough to make you throw up.
-Touch starved. Will want to be held but will quite literally break your arm if you try to touch her. If she can't, she will stay maskless for two days. Aiming to give either you or your companions nightmares. 
-Will never wear a shoe for the life of her.

rows.titleText: Now we know what made you what you are crimson. Now let us get to the meat of the story. What events changed the history of your world and what role did you play in them? Once you start a saga you must see It through, take only those you trust yourself to complete.

rows.title: First saga
rows.titleText:
You and your companions had just finished a harrowing adventure that involved, a donkey, obscene amounts of rope and a single gold coin. Why were these three crucial to the success of your latest tale in a story for another day? No, what mattered was spending your latest payout on as much booze and food as you could. The atmosphere was light in the tavern where you chose to drink away your earnings. Friends surrounded you, their tales washing over you as they spoke with delight. The mead was sweet, the ale was sour and the food was plenty steeped with flavour. It was a good night.
 
A scream tore through the festive mood. The hiss of blades leaving their sheathes filled the vacuum like the hiss of a dozen vipers. 

The first one came through the window, the second through the window. The third and fourth you missed as dozens more filled whatever crevasse there be. They were creatures of mutilated flesh and red-glowing veins. An undead the likes you'd sever seen before. Flame, arrow and blade engulfed their forms as every adventurer in the room raced to put them down. Wave after wave they came you watched as the young and inexperienced fell first under the onslaught. You watched as the barmaid who'd only just poured you a drink had her through ripped off.

objects.title: The maskfiend twins.
objects.text:
You will soon find out that the mask are slowly killing the twins. There are two ways of counteracting this. One is finding a warlock strong enough to unbound them from their masks. This will be painful and would leave the twins emotionally stunted for a few weeks. Closely watch over them, for Groko will end the world by taking off his mask after growing tired of wearing it. Krogo will slowly destroy themselves looking for every drug and drink under the sun so as to feel something once more. 
The other way is to defeat their Father.
He is a reason the twins are strong. Their Father was a great warlock who wanted a legacy of strong children. Imparted lessons and eldritch teaching that left the twins broken and scarred afterwards. Expect to face magiks and runes that would put the powers of both twins to shame.
You will face many of her failed experiments each wearing unique masks with unique effects. Each is mad and in a constant state of agony. There will be four of these stronger than the rest. These are the siblings of the twins, each in a state of constant madness and agony. Killing them will be difficult even more so if you want to subdue them. However, if you are versed in magiks or runes it will be easier stop them. If not good luck this will be trying you will not come out and scathed. Gain the chronic pain drawback(One of the siblings will slam your back against the ground). It will last for a year.

objects.title: The family of flamehaired.
objects.text:
Sera’s mother is a great warlord, the emerald fields shudder at the mention of the name flamehaired. For all her children are great warriors. Sera being the runt of the litter. For decades now Warlord flaimhaired has tried to make the emerald fields her own. Sending army upon army of her country men after the fields. The body count is of such a magnitude that in the coming year the emerald fields will soon be called the scarlet rot. Any more bloodshed and the fields will not bare food for decades if not generations. For his ill-conceived war has cost both sides deeply. An accord was reached by those that weren’t cowed or bribed by the flamehaired.  As well as the mintori who tire of the war and would like to return to the fields to till. 
Sera will ask you to accompany her to right the wrong she participated in. Expect to meet opposition from Sera’s siblings, her eldest brother a kind man with a heart of could and mommy issues will be your final challenger. He has the pankration greater ability. 
There are two ways to go about this one if you have the pankration perk you can go toe to toe with him trading blow for blow. Until one of you yields. Will take every you have to keep up with him. By the end of the fight, you will be victorious. Head bloodied but unbowed. Though the exhaustion and injuries will take their toll. You will collapse and Sera’s mother will take the opportunity to attack both you and her. Sera will defend on you and defeat her mother though she will be injured and cannot accompany you for one quest. 
If Sera instead fights her sibling the battle will be great. All will bear witness as the flaimhaired defeats champion after champion until it is time to defeat her brother. The fight wil be great shaing the very ground beneath your feet. The clans will watch, the mintori will watch, you will watch as Sera takes blow after blow. Refusing to spill her sibling’s blood. Sera will be a bloodied and broken mess but will remain standing. Her brother will refuse to kill her and no other champion will stand against her. They will be impressed by her resilience and determination. The clans will awestruck whispering the name flaimehaired with respect. Seeing the tide turn against her Sera’s mother will attack gravely wounding Sera brother. Seeing this the rage that she had kept hidden will explode forth. Though this  will not be a blind rage. This will awaken the greater rage within Sera. All that pain all that misery from all those hears of fighting and killing will explode forth. Sera will break her mother, blow after blow, strike after strike until she surrenders.

objects.title: Destruction of the jade horde
objects.text: Kenassa will come to you one day. She has found those who enslaved and killed her family. The jade hoard is a group of slavers, rapists and murderers. They prowl the lands marauding and killing. She wants your help to end their cruel games. You will have to find their base of operations an island far offshore.

objects.title: Fiendmask
objects.text:
You get a power like Krogo, though your summons are blood red. It will be a painful experience having the mask bonded to your soul. It will hurt, you will be left a reck. You will have nightmare every two weeks for the first two years. A part of your soul will be carved out to make the mask. 
You will be able summon your emotions like beasts. There appearance will vary wildly, however they will each be very powerful. Depending on what emotion you feel the strongest. If you bottle your emotions without faces them. You will starve the beasts. Once starved long enough they will break free of the mask and devour all that is before them. Though if you deal with your emotions accept them for what they are in the moment. Then your beasts will become stronger for it. The goal is not to defeat them or chain them. But to accept them as a part of yourself. To wear this mask is a commitment. A commitment to none other than yourself and the crimson.

objects.title: The rune bound book.
objects.text: Once you start reading the book you will go mad for exactly 7hours7minutes and 7 seconds. Your mind will be open to all the knowledge the maskmaker. This wisdom will he over a century old, your mind is not ready for it. After time of madness is over some of your memories will be missing replaced with that of the maskmaker. You will have only a fraction of their knowledge on runes, though this knowledge will give you an edge in runemagiks. One that would have taken you decades to gain. After seven days your memories will return the knowledge having been integrated within.

objects.title: Twins loyalty
objects.text:
Seeing their Father either dead or defeat will give them some closure. The twins will start their long journey of healing. Krogo will be less of an ass, her anger will be directed on those deserving. Groko will no longer cry himself to sleep, he will no longer hate his face and one day be able to take of the mask without ending the world. The twins will also be grateful if you subdued their siblings without killing them. They will leave your group for a year, so as to settle their siblings. You may join the twins though you cannot take any other quests during this time. During this time they will heal as a family, growing accustomed to the stray hug here and here. Every stray touch between you and the twins will start to last always a little longer. Soon Krogo growing every more daring and interested. On the final year Groko will quiet literally jump you and drag you to their bed. 
Groko will be calmer and gentler, constantly asking if you ‘like this’ or ‘want it this way’.
If you aren’t interested in that the twins will consider you family. And will trust you with their lives. You may take an additional sibling from the end as a companions for free. They will join you on your journey.
